# external-trap-miner seed list (#0133) — OPERATOR-CURATED.
#
# Format: one "<git_url> <ecosystem>" per line. Blank lines and lines starting
# with # are ignored. The ecosystem token is operator metadata (repo selection
# only); the miner does not branch on it.
#
# SELECTION is a human decision — pick high-star, active repos in the corpus's
# zero-coverage ecosystems (React, React Native/Expo, Swift/iOS, Kotlin/Android,
# TS frontend). The miner does NOT crawl.
#
# The LICENSE GATE is enforced automatically: only repos whose GitHub-resolved
# SPDX id is in {MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD-2-Clause, BSD-3-Clause, ISC, 0BSD,
# Unlicense, WTFPL} are cloned+mined. Anything else (GPL/AGPL/LGPL/MPL/CC/
# NOASSERTION/none) is rejected before any clone — so a mistaken entry here is
# safe, it is simply skipped and logged.
#
# ROLLOUT is deliberately batched (charter: "don't fire-hose"): a large wave is
# days of judge budget. Run one small ecosystem batch at a time and let the
# validate pipeline drain before the next.
#
# Verified-permissive starting examples (SPDX confirmed via the GitHub API
# 2026-07-08). Uncomment / extend as you curate a batch:

# https://github.com/streamich/react-use React        # Unlicense
# https://github.com/pmndrs/zustand React              # MIT
# https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated ReactNative  # MIT
